---
// SPDX-License-Identifier: Elastic-2.0

// Real signed verdicts from prod: the same length-only password validator
// handed to the gate in five languages. Four suites are too weak to certify
// (a length-only test can't notice a dropped digit/uppercase rule); Go is
// corral's own SQL guard — a genuinely thorough suite — and certifies clean.
// Rendered as plain theme-aware HTML/CSS: no images, no external requests,
// nothing to fetch (the site's test-enforced zero-external-requests posture).
const verdicts = [
  { lang: 'Python',     status: 'needs-review', survivors: 5, rec: 14, note: 'missing test written & proven' },
  { lang: 'Ruby',       status: 'needs-review', survivors: 6, rec: 15, note: 'missing test written & proven' },
  { lang: 'JavaScript', status: 'needs-review', survivors: 7, rec: 16, note: 'missing test written & proven' },
  { lang: 'TypeScript', status: 'needs-review', survivors: 6, rec: 19, note: 'missing test written & proven' },
  { lang: 'Go',         status: 'certified',    survivors: 0, rec: 13, note: "corral's own SQL guard — a genuinely thorough suite" },
];
---
<section class="section wide" id="proof-band">
  <h2>One blind spot, five languages, five signed verdicts</h2>
  <p class="lede">
    We handed corral the same toy password validator in five languages, each
    guarded by a single length-only test — the kind that ships green and
    notices nothing. The same blind spot was found, and the missing test
    handed back, in every one. <strong>~40s each. Every verdict signed.</strong>
    The one suite that certifies is corral's own — a genuinely thorough one.
  </p>

  <ul class="verdicts" role="list">
    {verdicts.map((v) => (
      <li class={`verdict ${v.status === 'certified' ? 'is-certified' : 'is-review'}`}>
        <span class="lang">{v.lang}</span>
        <span class="pill">{v.status}</span>
        <span class="detail">
          {v.status === 'certified'
            ? <span>{v.note} · <strong>0 survivors</strong></span>
            : <span><strong>{v.survivors} survivors</strong> · {v.note}</span>}
        </span>
        <span class="rec">rec {v.rec}</span>
      </li>
    ))}
  </ul>

  <div class="cta">
    <p class="cta-label">One command — off a single <code>ANTHROPIC_API_KEY</code>:</p>
    <pre class="cmd">corral certify --local --code validator.py \
  --goal "reject passwords under 8 chars, or missing a digit or an uppercase letter" \
  -- pytest</pre>
    <p class="cta-foot">
      Every number above is a real signed record you can verify offline —
      <a href="/field-notes/your-tests-suck/">read the three-verdict write-up →</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .wide { max-width: 1100px; }
  .lede { max-width: 760px; }

  .verdicts { list-style: none; margin: 28px 0 0; padding: 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 10px; }
  .verdict {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 130px 132px 1fr auto;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 14px;
    background: var(--panel);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 14px 18px;
  }
  .verdict.is-review { border-left-color: var(--amber); }
  .verdict.is-certified { border-left-color: var(--green); }

  .lang { font-weight: 700; font-size: 1.02rem; color: var(--fg); }

  .pill {
    justify-self: start;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 4px 12px;
    border-radius: 999px;
    border: 1px solid transparent;
  }
  .is-review .pill { color: var(--amber); background: var(--sel); border-color: var(--amber); }
  .is-certified .pill { color: var(--green); background: var(--sel); border-color: var(--green); }

  .detail { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.9rem; }
  .detail strong { color: var(--fg); }

  .rec {
    justify-self: end;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
  }

  .cta { margin-top: 28px; }
  .cta-label { margin: 0 0 8px; color: var(--fg); }
  .cta-label code { background: var(--sel); border-radius: 4px; padding: 1px 5px; font-size: 0.85em; }
  .cmd {
    background: var(--panel); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 14px 18px; overflow-x: auto; font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;
    font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--fg); margin: 0;
  }
  .cta-foot { margin: 12px 0 0; color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.9rem; }
  .cta-foot a { font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; }
  .cta-foot a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

  /* Stack the row on narrow viewports so nothing overflows the page body. */
  @media (max-width: 620px) {
    .verdict { grid-template-columns: 1fr auto; row-gap: 8px; }
    .detail { grid-column: 1 / -1; }
    .rec { justify-self: end; }
  }
</style>
